In multivariate analysis, the risk of infections was higher after allo-HCT (HR=18.0; 
 p<0.001) than auto-HCT. In allo-HCT patients, the risk was higher in acute leukemia patients vs other (HR=1.9; 
 p<0.001), MUD vs MSD (HR=2.6; 
 p<0.001), MMUD (mismatched unrelated donor) vs MSD (HR=4.2; 
 p<0.001), acute and chronic graft versus host disease (a/cGVHD) before infection (HR=1.9; 
 p<0.001 and HR=3.4; 
 p<0.001, respectively) (
 Table 2).
